THE KZN Health prayer day held at Addington Hospital in Durban was a much needed spiritual upliftment for departmental staff.This was voiced jointly by Health MEC Dr Sibongiseni Dhlomo and healthcare workers who attended the prayers on Monday. Dhlomo said they needed divine intervention following numerous tragic incidents which had claimed the lives of nurses and doctors over the past years. if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsuB1zU9laSK_bJrgzWXR_wgSZcLoFeC_sms9cllaNVOV_DLS3BaE-w_38D1Src2aofTp5mBfpz5KpY6k2YUvShBPUs4uYi1reu-T7cMDun5-i8nChdQqw-vAvxozxtwFL6WLIOzGmgkQiJseoyH7RM_vclb58OyFA1W24fahTkgUyn5-PdA6vk0szrcEFRTD0_PwADgXiImJ5czE05kRNJ70lHPNtD8jYrBfkPD53jxqUPpf4i3PKMNLiYsvjS91YyHPcV3e0eDvpF1xM_JXhIW7K3wN18\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzI9UpJ08zObZEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
